<HEADLINE>
BOTTOM LINE: SWANSON MOVED
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CHRIS BRANAM  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The trouble with Brennen Swanson? He's too
valuable.
</P>
<P>
   Swanson, Cal State Northridge's standout linebacker who had 15{
sacks last year, hasn't had the same success pressuring the
quarterback through three games, with only a half-sack.
</P>
<P>
   Swanson, a senior who is a half-sack away from tying the
school's career record of 20, hasn't had as many opportunities for
sacks because he's athletic enough to go into coverage.
</P>
<P>
   With just five sacks as a team, CSUN's defensive coaches are
making an adjustment for Saturday's Big Sky Conference game against
Idaho State.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're going to put (Swanson) on the line a little more,''
defensive line coach David Robinson said. ``We're going to keep him
inside, to rush the passer.''
</P>
<P>
   It makes sense to put Swanson back at the end of the line as a
pass-rushing specialist on a defense that has allowed 119 points
and 1,255 yards in its last two games, both losses.
</P>
<P>
   ``You put me at defensive end,'' he said, ``and that's the only
thing I need to do: get sacks.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Injury report: Sophomore safety Hassan Adbul-Malik (pulled
hamstring) was in full pads but probably won't play until the
Montana game on Oct. 9.
</P>
<P>
   Senior center Julio Alcala (back) didn't practice. ``He's got a
back that's chronically tender,'' Kearin said, ``and I want him for
Saturdays.''
</P>
<P>
   Senior tailback Jaumal Bradley has tonsillitis and is doubtful
for Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Levi Line, a starting defensive lineman, has a strained tendon
in his left knee and might not play this week. Two other defensive
starters, safety Rahman Sparks (ribs) and defensive end Jason Mageo
(ankle), are also doubtful for Idaho State.
</P>
</TEXT>
