<P>
   ED-GOPSPENDING _ Republican majorities on Capitol Hill look like
the Gang Who Can't Legislate Straight. For the umpteenth time,
they've failed to pass crucial spending bills and have had to
resort to continuing resolutions to keep the government running.
Problem lies squarely with their own infighting and their
ideologically driven poison pill riders. (Geshwiler, Atlanta
Constitution). 8
</P>
