   FERGIE _ ATLANTA _ She probably wouldn't serve a meal on Chinet,
but Sarah Ferguson, the Duchess of York, is quite comfortable,
thank you very much, entertaining in a less stuffy fashion than
that to which her ex-in-laws are accustomed. The former wife of
Britain's Prince Andrew is the new U.S. spokeswoman for Wedgwood,
the British maker of tableware, and on Wednesday she was in Atlanta
to give a table decorating demo. at Rich's. She also talked about
life since Liz, her talks with NBC about becoming a ``Today'' show
correspondent and why she prefers ``easy elegance'' when it comes
to breaking bread. (Flanders, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
