<P>
   FOOD
</P>
<P>
   COXNET FOOD PAGE
</P>
<P>
   EDS: This is the CoxNet FOOD page for the current week. This
layout is now available.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET FOOD 0928 _ It's now or never. Unless you relish paying
winter prices of $2.99 when you need just one red bell pepper, this
i
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 to 2 tablespoons peanut oil
</P>
<P>
   Bake sweet potatoes until soft and mashable. Scoop out insides,
place in an oiled casserole dish and sprinkle with dill weed. Steam
or microwave cauliflower. Break up into pieces and sprinkle with
the dry red wine. Cut tofu into cubes. Heat oil in a large frying
pan. Add chopped garlic. When the garlic is sizzling, add tofu and
lightly brown. Mix tofu and cauliflower with undiluted canned cream
soup, peanut butter, yogurt, dill weed and chives. Place the cooled
tofu mixture on top of the sweet potatoes. Slice tomato. Place in a
single layer on top of the casserole. Sprinkle with basil. Bake
covered at 350 degrees for 20 minutes; uncover and bake 10 minutes
more.
</P>
<P>
   RICE AND BEAN PILAF
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup dried pinto beans
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup dried whole peas
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup dried lentils
</P>
<P>
   1 quart vegetable broth
</P>
<P>
   2 carrots, thinly sliced
</P>
<P>
   2 stalks celery, thinly sliced
</P>
<P>
   1 onion, chopped
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon olive oil
</P>
<P>
   2 bay leaves
</P>
<P>
   1 cup V-8 juice
</P>
<P>
   Basil, parsley, cilantro, freshly ground pepper, ground
coriander seed to taste
</P>
<P>
   1 cup uncooked white or brown rice
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup uncooked wild rice
</P>
<P>
   Soak pinto beans, whole peas and lentils overnight. Drain. Cover
with water to about an inch above the legumes. Bring to a boil. Add
vegetable stock and bay leaves. Return to a boil and then reduce to
simmer. Saute carrots, celery and onion in olive oil until soft.
Add vegetables to the broth and beans. Add V-8 juice, season with
basil, parsley, cilantro and ground coriander seed and freshly
ground pepper to taste. Add brown and wild rice. Bring to a boil.
Reduce to simmer. Cook until the rice is soft and the liquid is
absorbed. Serve with a green salad.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analyses not available.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
