<P>
   LIFE IN AMERICA: Couple swaps Florida for Fairbanks
</P>
<P>
   FAIRBANKS, Alaska _ In 1996, Terry and Jane Reilly forsook their
homes in West Palm Beach, Fla., to live much of their lives in
brutal cold and unending darkness. And when I say forsook, I mean
forsook. ``We accepted a 60 percent cut in income to move here,''
says Jane, 44, a longtime sunny Florida resident and former
insurance agent with her family's business, Sam Irvine &AMP;
Associates. ``We came for the job, not the weather. Terry teaches
Shakespeare at the University of Alaska. We love it here.'' The
extreme cold isn't so bad, the Reillys say. But their protests
sound suspiciously like Arizonans' apologies for their ``dry''
heat. ``It's a dry cold,'' explains Terry. ``And Fairbanks is in a
valley sheltered by two mountain ranges, so there's very little
wind.'' (Wiggins, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
