<P>
   FOOD-BRAZIL _ SAO PAULO, Brazil _ The final leg of Wendell
Brock's Brazilian journey finds him in Sao Paulo, where Dona Nair
Galvao da Silva has invited him into her home for a typical
Paulista lunch. He was expecting coffee and dessert but found a
groaning table laid with four different meats, rice, beans, fried
yucca, heart of palm salad and five desserts. It is a sweet ending
to two-week journey in which the writer has discovered the rich,
African-flavored dishes of the states of Bahia and Minas Gerais,
which parallel the food traditions of the American South, and the
straightforward Portuguese style of the Moreira kitchen. A
discussion of the history and the distinctive ingredients of
Brazilian cookery. With recipes for main courses, side dishes, a
salad and desserts. Brock. (Brock, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
WITH COLOR PHOTO.
