   JEWISH-COOKING _ DAYTON, Ohio _ ``Sukkot, the Feast of
Tabernacles, was the most important thanksgiving festival,''
explains Marc Gruber, senior rabbi at Dayton's Temple Israel. The
Pilgrims modeled their Thanksgiving on Sukkot.'' The sukkah is a
place for festive gatherings: Families often eat meals there during
the holiday and invite friends to share the celebration. ``Each
Jewish holiday has special foods associated with it and has aspects
that are religious, historical and seasonal,'' says Gruber, who
last year invited his entire congregation to an open house in his
sukkah. WITH PHOTOS. MOVED.
