<P>
   Managing editors, news editors, business editors:
</P>
<P>
   This is a reminder that in the next few days Bloomberg News will
no longer be available through  &UR; The New York Times News Service &LR; .
Bloomberg has elected to become a paid service.
</P>
<P>
   As we promised in our advisory last week, The New York Times
News Service will continue to bring you the best of business
coverage from established sources. The Times itself provides one of
the most accurate, complete and authoritative worldwide business
reports anywhere. The News Service will continue to supplement The
Times's coverage with regional business reports provided by partner
news organizations, including The Boston Globe, the Hearst
Newspapers, the Cox Newspapers and The San Francisco Chronicle.
</P>
<P>
   In addition, new coverage is being planned and new partnerships
will be announced shortly.
</P>
<P>
   We regret any inconvenience that Bloomberg's decision to charge
separately for its report causes you. As a service to clients, we
will continue to provide Bloomberg News on our wire as long as
Bloomberg makes it available to us.
</P>
