<HEADLINE>
IN A LEAGUE OF HER OWN 
</HEADLINE>
   (EDs: Filed in the commentary, ``k,'' and the sports, ``s,''
categories)  
 Commentary  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By ROB MORSE  
 c.1999 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ For those trying to score tickets to the last
San Francisco Giants game at Candlestick Park on Thursday, Sherry
Davis has a question: ``Where were you on a cold Tuesday night
against Montreal?''
</P>
<P>
   Davis, the Giants' biggest fan with the loudest yet gentlest
voice at Candlestick Park, also said, ``They could have gone this
past weekend. It was beautiful.''
</P>
<P>
   Not that a big crowd is a better crowd.
</P>
<P>
   ``Sometimes when we have a full house of 40,000 people it isn't
as good a crowd as when we have 8,000 people,'' she said. ``Some of
our best crowds are the small ones. Then you have the really
responsive fans.''
</P>
