</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN (Washington) _ The fight among Republican
presidential candidates is a classic battle between the forces of
centrism and those of the right. We look at the history of such
conflicts since 1912. It shows that the side that wins one year
does not prevail forever. By ROBERT E. THOMPSON. (For release
Sunday, Oct. 3.)
</P>
