ESCALON, Calif. _  &UR; SOURCE-Nuts &LR;  _ At John Lagier's fruit and nut
ranch in California's Central Valley, the almond harvest is under
way. His 36 acres of almond trees near this San Joaquin County town
are like a grain of sand on the beach when compared to the 480,000
acres planted throughout the state. But Lagier is an industry
leader, one of a growing number of almond farmers who are trying to
dramatically reduce the use of pesticides.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; By Janet Fletcher &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle &QL;  &LR; 
