<P>
   APARTMENT-MAKEOVER (New York) _ Historically, New York is a town
of temporary residences people inhabit with the false permanence
that prevails in prisons. Or in college. With living-room laissez
faire, perfectly capable adults cultivate a casual grad-school look
long after the paperback Voltaire has been shelved behind the
hardcover ``Fight Aging with Antioxidants.'' The House &AMP; Home
section asked four top interior designers to take their skills and
tackle three real-life scenarios that the celebrity clients and
decorator show houses never expose you to. By William A. Hamilton
and Stephen Williams.
</P>
