<P>
   &UR; WRESTLING &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   WCW _ ATLANTA: Some home cookin' seems to have hit the spot for
the WCW. There was a giddy buzz backstage at the sparkling new
Philips Arena, future home of the Atlanta Hawks and Atlanta
Thrashers. As ``Monday Nitro'' wrestlers and roadies shuttled back
and forth, the upbeat mood was apparent. In the arena, thousands of
shouting fans were shaking the walls to welcome a new World
Championship Wrestling back home for this week's show. The show was
the first televised event under the stewardship of Bill Busch.
(WITH PHOTOS)
</P>
<P>
   WRESTLING: UNFORGIVEN: You'll have to forgive me if I didn't
walk away from the World Wrestling Federation's latest pay-per-view
event _ ``Unforgiven'' less than impressed. Maybe I expect a little
more. A little more action, a little more excitement, a little more
imagination and a few more surprises from Vinny Mac and the boys
from Titan Towers. (WITH PHOTO)
</P>
<P>
   WRESTLING: RAIL: Brief items of interest, including bios, TV
info, etc.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NASCAR &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   NASCAR 1001: Mark Martin won at Dover on Sunday, but owner Jack
Roush was more pleased with the performance of driver Matt Kenseth,
who finished fourth. Kenseth, one of the best on the Busch circuit,
joins the Roush team next season. And he's ready.
</P>
