<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Mini views
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  ``My Favorite Martian'' (PG) _ A big-screen remake of the '60s
TV series, with the annoying and unsubtle Christopher Lloyd as the
Martian who camps in Jeff Daniels' living room. The movie is
cobbled together with cheesy special effects and easy gags. But for
kids, it's an OK baby sitter. Grade: C
</P>
<P>
   _Steve Murray
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Hands on a Hard Body'' (PG) _ S.R. Bindler's riveting 1997
documentary unfolds primarily in a tent set in the parking lot of a
Nissan showroom in smalltown Texas. It's here that 23 lucky
contestants jockey to win a new, $15,000 truck. All they have to do
is be the last one standing beside it, with one hand touching the
vehicle. The more time we spend under that tent, the more nobility
and depth director-editor Bindler finds in these people. Grade: A-
</P>
<P>
   _Steve Murray
</P>
