<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Spotlight on Brendan Fraser
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Encino Man'' (1992; PG). Thawing out and cutting loose as a
prehistoric man encountering life in a '90s high school.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``School Ties'' (1992; PG-13). Facing anti-Semitism in a
preppy '50s private school in a class that includes Matt Damon, Ben
Affleck and Chris O'Donnell.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``With Honors'' (1994; PG-13). Learning life lessons from
homeless Joe Pesci.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Blast from the Past'' (1999; PG-13). Growing up underground
with squeaky '50s-era parents Christopher Walken and Sissy Spacek.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Airheads'' (1994; PG-13). As a would-be rock star, hijacking
a radio station.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``George of the Jungle'' (1997; PG ). Failing to watch out for
that tree.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Gods and Monsters'' (1998; R). Building an odd friendship
with gay director James Whale (Ian McKellen) in this Hollywood
drama.
</P>
<P>
   THE VIDEO COLLECTOR
</P>
