   POLITICAL NEWS (``p'' category)
</P>
<P>
   GORE-2000 (Washington) _ Vice President Al Gore says he faces a
``hard, tough fight'' for the Democratic presidential nomination,
and vows to challenge opponent Bill Bradley to a series of debates.
By BENNETT ROTH.
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-2000 (Bakersfield, Calif.) _ Republican presidential
front-runner George W. Bush, in an animated news conference that
showed his competitive nature, says he wants Pat Buchanan to stay
in the Republican Party so Bush can ``whip `im'' in the primaries.
By R.G. RATCLIFFE.
