<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BBN-ASTROS (Houston) _ Mired in their worst slump of the season
at the worst possible time with eight losses in their past 11
games, the Houston Astros try to regain a share of first place in
the National League Central as they wrap up a two-game series
against Cincinnati at the Astrodome. By CARLTON THOMPSON.
</P>
<P>
   With: BBN-ROBERTSON-COLUMN, BBN-ASTROREAX and BBN-REDS
</P>
<P>
   HKN-STARS (Dallas) _ The defending Stanley Cup champion Dallas
Stars have savored their controversial championship for months, and
now they say they are primed to go out and defend the title when
the NHL season begins Friday. By BILL SULLIVAN.
</P>
<P>
   For Sunday:
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN (Washington) _ The fight among Republican
presidential candidates is a classic battle between the forces of
centrism and those of the right. We look at the history of such
conflicts since 1912. It shows that the side that wins one year
does not prevail forever. By ROBERT E. THOMPSON. (For release
Sunday, Oct. 3.)
</P>
