<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Find-it guide
 &HT;    By Marylin Johnson
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Having trouble finding a particular item? We'll try to
help you locate it. But due to the volume of mail, we cannot track
down every request. Readers whose queries are answered in the
column will receive a blue-and-cream canvas Buyer's Edge tote bag.
Write us at Buyer's Edge Find It, Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
P.O. Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302; e-mail us at
buyersedge(at)ajc.com (please include your name, the city you live
in and daytime phone number); or call 404-582-7642.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am looking for McCormick's pasta primavera sauce in an
envelope.
</P>
<P>
   _Carol Walker, Sautee (Ga.)
</P>
<P>
   Another McCormick request: I just found out that McCormick no
longer makes its Cincinnati Chili Mix. Can you find a substitute?
</P>
<P>
   _Sally Morris, Conyers (Ga.)
</P>
<P>
   And another plea: I have been looking for Taco Casserole by
McCormick. It's in a green box that has the tomato sauce, chips and
seasoning. All I do is add hamburger and cheese. Any clue?
</P>
<P>
   _Charles Ballentine, Peachtree City (Ga.)
</P>
<P>
   A: It sounds as if all good cooks are gearing up for yummy fall
eating. First, the Primavera Pasta Sauce Blend: It comes in a
1.2-ounce envelope and at times can be hard to find. We discovered
our envelope for $1.39 at Publix, 1544 Piedmont Ave N.E.
(404-898-1850).
</P>
<P>
   Both the Cincinnati Chili Mix and the Taco Casserole in a box
have been discontinued. However, McCormick has made the recipes
available via its consumer line: 1-800-632-5847. Or look for the
chili recipe on the company's Web site at www.mccormick.com. Hint:
The Cincinnati Chili is a sweet-spicy recipe that contains cloves,
chili powder and cinnamon. Also, McCormick makes a line of chili
seasonings, including the Original Chili Seasoning in a 1.25-ounce
envelope for about $1.19. It's widely available in grocery stores.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Will you assist me in locating Vivienne's Romano Cheese
Dressing? I used to buy the dressing at the Publix store on Roswell
Road, but it has been missing from the shelf for the past month.
</P>
<P>
   _ Naudja Threadgill, Roswell (Ga.)
</P>
<P>
   A: Thomas Tucker of St. Louis, Mo., who owns and produces the
Vivienne Romano Cheese Dressing, says his dressing has been sold to
Publix in the past (item No. 786072). Tucker suggests you contact
the store manager and ask him or her to order it. Or you can order
the dressing directly from the company. Twelve 8-ounce bottles (one
case) are $33 plus shipping and handling (1-800-827-0778). This
made-from-scratch gourmet dressing has been a favorite of St. Louis
folks since 1948. Ingredients include Romano cheese, vinegar,
hard-cooked egg and a blend of spices.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I've been looking for Clairol's True to Light makeup mirror.
I had one when I was a teen but haven't seen one recently. Can you
help?
</P>
<P>
   _ Melanie Zito, Newnan (Ga.)
</P>
<P>
   A: Mirror, mirror on the wall. ... You will soon be the fairest
of all with the True to Light makeup mirror by _ Remington. Several
years ago, the company bought the rights to this mirror from
Clairol and now markets it under the Remington name. We found the
mirror (style No. LM7, $29.99) at the Remington Factory Service
Center store in Perimeter Mall (770-395-7441).
</P>
<P>
   Q: For my husband's Christmas gift, I am trying to locate a pair
of red pajamas with ``feet'' (the kind that you envision toddlers
wearing). I called J Crew, the Gap and JC Penney, to no avail.
Maybe your search will be more successful than mine.
</P>
<P>
   _Tara Reeves, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   A: There's a bit of kid in all of us, right? Warmth Wear LLC is
a family-owned business in Idaho selling these cozy, comfy adult
``footed jammies'' through its Web site, www.srv.net
</P>
<P>
   /(tilde)wwear/wwear.html. Made from Polar Fleece or cotton
flannel, they come in all colors and a variety of prints and
patterns, sized extra small to extra large. Each pair is $65. Those
with a drop seat, Moonies, are $75. You can also contact the
company by calling 1-888-300-7752 or writing Warmth Wear LLC, 175
Church St., Newdale, ID 83436-0185.
</P>
<P>
   Q: For a year or more, I have been unable to find Little
Debbie's Golden Almond granola bars. I have checked most major
stores. One friend located four boxes in a Kroger, and I managed to
barter some fresh home-grown tomatoes for one of the boxes! Unless
you take pity on me, I may never again have another delicious
Golden Almond granola bar.
</P>
<P>
   _ Mary Cicotello, Marietta (Ga.)
</P>
<P>
   A: How could we not help after that plea? We found Little Debbie
Golden Almond Chewy Granola Bars, owned by McKee Foods, at Publix,
1100 Hammond Drive, Dunwoody (Ga.) (678-443-2100). An 8-ounce box
(eight bars) is $1.59. They are also available, according to the
company, at Wal-Mart, 3100 Johnson Ferry Road, Marietta; and
Publix, 3605 Sandy Plains Road, Marietta. The bars are packaged
under the banner Sunbelt Snacks &AMP; Cereals, another McKee Foods
brand. And in teeny type on the front, it says, ``Baked by Little
Debbie Snacks.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Contributing: Michelle C. Brooks
</P>
