<P>
   GROWING-OLD (Abiquiu, N.M.) _ Talking about growing old and
dying has long been taboo in youth-obsessed America, but in coming
years, it may begin to seem as though older Americans talk of
little else. The generation that is retired and is approaching its
last years, and the baby boomers following them, are examining what
it means to age as no other generation has before. By Sara Rimer.
</P>
<P>
   NY-MUSEUM (New York) _ Moving on a new front against the
Brooklyn Museum of Art, the Giuliani administration said Wednesday
that it would move to terminate the museum's lease, citing several
factors including the fact that its 100-year lease with the city _
signed in 1894 _ was no longer in force. By David Herszenhorn and
David Barstow.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-INFANT-SLEEP (Undated) _ Children under 2 should never sleep
with their parents, the American Medical Association and Consumer
Product Safety Commission say in a study which is provoking furious
reactions from people on both sides. Over an eight-year period, the
researchers say, 515 babies and toddlers died in adult beds: 121
smothered when a parent rolled over on them and 394 were caught in
parts of the bed itself. By Erica Goode.
</P>
