</P>
<P>
   FBC-MEDIAGUIDES _ Once upon a time football media guides were
handy. They were as no nonsense as the crewcuts the players sported
and were chock full of useful statistics, records and correct
spellings. What's more, the four-ounce booklets were still svelte
enough that a sportswriter could tuck one in the back pocket of his
polyester pants, leaving his hands free to take notes or quotes.
Times sure have changed. The once unassuming media guide has become
the glitzy, gargantuan media/recruiting/fundraising guide. Forget
the pants pocket. Many guides now barely fit inside a big pocket in
a computer case. And they're growing every year. The University of
Colorado's guide swelled from 244 pages last year to 324 pages this
year. And that was after an 8-4 season and an Aloha Bowl bid.
(Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
