<P>
   GORE _ WASHINGTON _ Vice President Al Gore, looking for a way to
rejuvenate his Democratic presidential campaign, has decided to
move his political operation to his home state of Tennessee and
challenge his sole rival (Bradley) to a series of debates. Campaign
chairman Tony Coelho and chief strategeist Carter Eskew will move
to Nashville, but it is unclear how many members of his senior
staff will follow. (Shepard, Cox News Service).
