   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   CONGRESS-SS _ WASHINGTON _ Republican leaders repeatedly vowed
Wednesday not to spend ``one penny of the Social Security surplus
on anything other than Social Security.'' But with the new fiscal
year beginning Friday, they were preparing to engage in some
ingenious accounting. Budget experts warned of dangerous
consequences. (Malone, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   POLLUTE _ WASHINGTON _ AAA, the auto group, issues a report that
it says will prove that cars and trucks are not the leading source
of pollution in U.S. cities. In fact, AAA will say that cars are no
longer even a major contributor to ozone-causing emissions. (Hill,
Cox News Service). 20.
</P>
<P>
   HISPANICS-COLLEGE _ WASHINGTON - New policies intended to
increase the number of Hispanic Americans who get college
educations could raise their combined salaries by $130 billion a
year, says a study to be released and discussed Wednesday by
officials of the Hispanic Association of Colleges and Universities
and of Educational Testing Service, which is best known for
administering SAT tests. Some old ways are mentioned again and some
new methods are proposed for boosting the very small number of
Hispanic Americans who go to college. (Mollison, Cox News Service).
12.
