<P>
   BEANIES-JUDAIC (Los Angeles) _ Last winter while buying Beanie
Babies for his children's Hanukkah gifts, Steven Hoffman felt some
regret that the animal-shaped bags of beans didn't contain some
religious significance for his family. Within a few weeks, Hoffman
and a friend were developing a line of Judaic-themed beanbag
animals that went on sale last month. Their Chatsworth-based
Macca-Beanies LLC has already sold thousands of toys and expects to
exceed $300,000 in sales in the last quarter of this year. By Chris
Sieroty.
</P>
