<P>
   DEVIL-WINDS (Los Angeles) _ After an unusually dry summer and
spring, the wildfire season's first Santa Ana winds blow through
the San Fernando Valley, prompting an emergency deployment of 44
firefighters in the mountains. The humidity level is high, with
winds gusting to 15 mph. Temperatures were expected to hit 100 or
more in the San Fernando Valley. By Dominic Berbeo. (Will move in
the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news file.)
