<P>
   (NYT17) UNDATED -- Sept. 29, 1999 -- HOME-IMPROVEMENT-B&AMP;W, 09-29
-- If you do decide to use pressure-treated lumber for a project,
it is important to choose the boards carefully, observe all safety
precautions and wear safety gear. Wear gloves when handling the
lumber, and look for pieces with the fewest number of splits, wanes
and knots. Look carefully at the surface of the boards; they should
be free of any crystalline chemical residue. Try to choose dry
lumber. (Edward R. Lipinski/New York Times Photo) LITE
