Akamatsu, a Miwa spokesman, demonstrates locks that his company
advertises as effective against ``foreign theft gangs.'' The ad
campaign, which brought a burst of interest in Miwa locks, offers a
window on a deep streak in Japanese society to look askance at most
things foreign, especially fellow Asians. (Howard French/New York
Times Photo)
