   (NYT34) WASHINGTON -- Sept. 29, 1999 -- OBIT-CREWS-B&AMP;W, 09-29 --
John R. Crews at the 1948 ceremony where he received the Medal of
Honor. Crews, who as an Army sergeant in World War II won the medal
by single-handedly capturing a German automatic-weapons position
while severely wounded, died Saturday in Oklahoma City, his
hometown. He was 76. (New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT33) ROME -- Sept. 29, 1999 -- ROME-ANTIQUITIES, 09-29 --
Work on a ramp to a huge Vatican parking garage has been halted
while archaeologists uncover the walls of a villa dating from the
first century A.D. Conservationists want the ramp closed down and
the ruins resurrected. (James Hill/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT32) NEW YORK -- Sept. 29, 1999 -- NY-MUSEUM-3, 09-29 -- Mike
Soberanis paints a wall on Wednesday in the hall where the
``Sensation'' exhibit will be shown at the Brooklyn Museum. At left
is ``Eye Love Eye,'' an oil on canvas by Alain Miller which is part
of the exhibit. The battle over opening the exhibt moved into the
courts on Wednesday, with the museum claiming that artistic
expression is protected by the First Amendment and the city saying
taxpayers are not required to pay for offensive exhibits. (James
Estrin/New York Times Photo)
</P>
