-- Cynthia Nixon, left, and Amy Hohn in Douglas Carter Beane's
``Country Club'' at Greenwich House Theater. Both actresses are
playing seriously dissatisfied suburban women who are burdened with
material comfort, Protestant neuroses and silly nicknames and who,
approaching 30, just can't make that leap of faith from adolescence
to adulthood. (Sara Krulwich/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
