<P>
   (NYT11) NORTH TOP SAIL ISLAND, N.C. -- Sept. 29, 1999 --
HURRICANE CAROLINA, 09-29 -- Bill Brown comforts Marie Tyner after
she returned home Saturday afternoon to find that it was toppled by
a storm surge during Hurricane Floyd. Residents were allowed to
return to their homes on the island so they could assess damages
left by the storm. State officials announced plans on Wednesday to
spend up to $60 million to buy about 4,000 mobile homes for
displaced flood victims to live in for up to 18 months while their
homes are repaired or replaced. (Ken Blevins/Wilmington Star-News)
</P>
