is up to the job of stewarding one of the world's most valuable
brands.''
</P>
<P>
   Columnist John Rogers puts Home Depot on his list of ``stocks to
avoid,'' arguing that rising interest rates could hurt the company
in two ways: All high-priced stocks are susceptible to rising
rates, and higher rates may hurt the company's housing market.
</P>
