   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; FOR PAGE ONE SAN FRANCISCO CHRONICLE &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; BOFA _  &LR; A grim BankAmerica Chief Executive David Coulter telephoned
top deputies as he was winging his way back to San Francisco from a
European conference. His message: BofA must kill its pending merger
with North Carolina's NationsBank. Coulter's desperate move 16
months ago came after NationsBank's leader Hugh McColl insulted him
in a private conversation, a clash that left Coulter horrified and
unable to sleep. Coulter believed that the incident revealed
McColl's real intent. To the North Carolina banker, BofA was not an
equal partner, but the latest in a long line of conquests. By Sam
Zuckerman
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; FOR SAN FRANCISCO CHRONICLE BUSINESS SECTION &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; PRINTERS &LR;  _ Everybody is aware that PC prices have fallen below the
$1,000 mark _ in some cases well below _ but did you know that
printer prices have fallen almost as fast? Top-level manufacturers
such as HP, Canon, Epson and Lexmark now offer some models for
$49-79. So before you embark on the process, it pays to arm
yourself with some basic knowledge about the printer market, plus
some tips on sensible shopping. By Henry Norr
</P>
